DATE: 02/04/26
TASK: Fix Purchase CAPI not attributing to Ads Manager

---

PROBLEM

Meta Ads Manager showed 0 purchases despite CAPI events being received by Meta (Events Manager showed events_received: 1). Backend was firing Purchase events correctly but attribution was broken.

ROOT CAUSES IDENTIFIED

1. action_source: 'physical_store' in tripay-callback
   - This was the primary cause. Meta never attributes physical_store events to ad campaigns.
   - Only 'website' and 'app' action sources are counted in Ads Manager.
   - All Purchase events were being received by Meta but silently unattributed.

2. event_source_url: null on all Purchase events
   - Purchase fires from backend (tripay-callback), which has no knowledge of the user's landing URL.
   - Without the URL (which contains fbclid + UTM params), Meta cannot perform proper deduplication or attribution scoring.
   - global_product table had no page_url column to carry this forward from frontend.

3. fbc: null on some purchases (~40% of users)
   - handleFbcCookieManager() was only called inside initFacebookPixelWithLogging(), which runs after pixel JS loads asynchronously.
   - Fast-clicking users or users in Facebook in-app browser would submit payment before fbc was saved.

---

FIXES APPLIED

1. tripay-callback/index.ts
   - Changed action_source from 'physical_store' to 'website'
   - Added eventSourceUrl: order.page_url to the capi-universal invocation

2. tripay-create-payment/index.ts
   - Extracted pageUrl from request body
   - Saved page_url to global_product on insert

3. ai/src/universal/darkfeminine.tsx
   - Added pageUrl: window.location.href to the payment payload sent to tripay-create-payment
   - Added dedicated useEffect with empty deps [] calling handleFbcCookieManager() at component mount (before pixel loads) to ensure fbc is captured early

4. Database
   - Added page_url TEXT column to global_product table via Supabase Management API
   - Migration file: elvisiongroup/supabase/migrations/20260402_add_page_url_to_global_product.sql

5. Manual resend
   - Last purchase (Maria Fransiska, T4427232139978AXUGN, 02/04/26 17:46) was manually resent to Meta CAPI with correct action_source: 'website', fbc, and event_source_url
   - Same event_id used to prevent duplicate counting
   - Meta confirmed: events_received: 1, fbtrace_id: Antu7ddJS8UOV1E3bhxlF5x

6. App version bumped: 1.0.0 -> 1.0.1
   - npm run build completed successfully, 0 errors

